-- Deutsche Bank prices new shares above expectations
-- By Thomas Atkins
-- Thu Jun 05, 2014 06:06AM EDT
-- None



FRANKFURT, June 5 (Reuters) - Deutsche Bank <DBKGn.DE> priced its rights issue at 22.50 euros ($31.0) per share on Thursday, above expectations, raising more capital than initially anticipated to fortify its regulatory ratios and fund a restructuring.

The bank said it would issue 299.8 million new shares, offering five new shares for every 18 shares held by existing shareholders.